text: This is the web version of the WSJ’s daily economic newsletter. You can sign up for daily delivery here. Good morning! Today we look at a rather misshapen Phillips curve, a record number of U.S. job openings, the Trump administration’s decision to leave the Iran nuclear accord, a big mess in Argentina that the Fed (unintentionally) helped Why It's a Good Time to Look for a Job Next How a Supreme Court Decision This Spring Could Cut Union Rolls by 726,000
